---
import Brand from '../layouts/Brand.astro';
---
<Brand title="Templates · usejarvis" description="Every app Jarvis learns becomes a reusable YAML template. Builders contribute them, hosted users buy them — the marketplace turns software coverage into a revenue layer." active="templates">
  <header class="page-hero">
    <div class="page-hero-in">
      <span class="waitchip reveal reveal-up"><span class="d"></span>Marketplace · opens Q3–Q4 2026</span>
      <p class="label-mono reveal reveal-up">Templates</p>
      <h1 class="display-h1 reveal reveal-up">Every app becomes a <em>template.</em></h1>
      <p class="lead reveal reveal-up">A Jarvis template is one YAML file that teaches the agent to operate an app — targeting roles and ARIA, not screenshots, so it doesn't rot on the next UI refresh. Builders contribute them; hosted users request and buy them. Coverage compounds instead of decaying.</p>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:11px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-top:26px" class="reveal reveal-up">
        <a class="btn-solid" href="https://discord.gg/2HgF5krXrj" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Join the waitlist</a>
        <a class="btn-border" href="/builders">Build a template</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="section"><div class="section-inner">
    <div class="feat-grid reveal reveal-up">
      <div class="feat"><span class="fk">Browse</span><span class="ft">Install in one line</span><span class="fp">Pull a community template and Jarvis can drive that app immediately — <b>no MCP server, no API key, no integration work.</b></span></div>
      <div class="feat"><span class="fk">Build</span><span class="ft">Write it once in YAML</span><span class="fp">Describe the app's tasks in roles and ARIA. Ship to the marketplace <b>without waiting for a release.</b></span></div>
      <div class="feat"><span class="fk">Request</span><span class="ft">Ask for any app</span><span class="fp">Need an app that isn't covered yet? Request it — a builder picks it up, and <b>everyone gets the coverage.</b></span></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section section-alt"><div class="section-inner">
    <p class="label-mono reveal reveal-up">Why a marketplace</p>
    <h2 class="display-h2 reveal reveal-up" style="margin:12px 0 14px">Coverage is the moat, <em>not a feature.</em></h2>
    <p class="lead reveal reveal-up">API/MCP agents stay capped at whatever vendors choose to expose, and shrink as vendors deprecate. The native path goes the other way: every app a human can use is reachable, and the community ships integrations faster than any single engineering team. The template inventory turns that coverage into a revenue layer (70/30 split, builders earn).</p>
    <div class="cta-band reveal reveal-up" style="margin-top:30px">
      <div class="ctitle">The marketplace is the heart of the moat.</div>
      <div class="csub">It opens Q3–Q4 2026. Join the waitlist, or start building templates now and be first to supply it.</div>
      <div class="cact"><a class="btn-solid" href="https://discord.gg/2HgF5krXrj" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Join the waitlist</a><a class="btn-border" href="/builders">Become a builder</a></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>
</Brand>
